the first national bank of layton is a locally owned and operated bank in layton, utah. fnb of layton was established in 1905 when the founders pooled together $25,000 to open a community bank. the bank has seven branches throughout the wasatch front. the first national bank of layton’s current chairman, kevin garn, was named to the position in 2000. k. john jones was appointed as president and ceo in 2007. the first national bank’s first location, designed by self-trained architect william allen, is on the national register of historic places. it is one of only six utah banks that have stayed in business for over one hundred years.